        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-15 14:54:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nI still think the navigation on this new look-and-feel is ultimately a step backward.\n\n1) When you navigate into a section, there is no equivalent to the left-hand nav that exists in the current design.  For example, if I drill into the requirements list for VNF Requirements (Current: https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/casablanca/submodules/vnfrqts/requirements.git/docs/Chapter9/index.html  vs. Proposed: https://logs.onap.org/production/vex-yul-ecomp-jenkins-1/doc-master-verify-rtd/4714/html/submodules/vnfrqts/requirements.git/docs/Chapter9/index.html) you'll see there's no way to navigate elsewhere within the VNF Requirements Documentation Section.  Your only recourse is to back out or go directly to another top-level section and drill down again.  \n\n2) The page size is much narrower and text is smaller than on the current theme.  \n\n3) The requirement blocks in the VNFRQTS project render with unusual indentation and the requirement IDs are very small and more challenging to read.   \n\n4) The table formatting seems to lack formatting between the rows and columns (see Proposed: https://logs.onap.org/production/vex-yul-ecomp-jenkins-1/doc-master-verify-rtd/4714/html/submodules/vvp/documentation.git/docs/validation-scripts.html vs. Current: https://docs.onap.org/en/latest/submodules/vvp/documentation.git/docs/validation-scripts.html)\n\nDoes this theme have to ability to address these items via configuration?",
        "patchset_number": 7
      },
